FilmTec Corp, a subsidiary of DowChemical Co, said the Food and Drug Administration willpermitthe FilmTec FT30 reverse osmosis membrane to be used in foodprocessing and purifying water for food applications.    The company said the development opens "a potentially hugemarket for FilmTec." It said food processors will be able toconcentrate juice and other food streams with reverse osmosisrather than with evaporation techniques. Reuter&#3;